***Richmond Techs DeLa Cruz/Koonjun removed the elevator from service to land car, get oil [Piston Seal & Valve  Replacement/ Richmond SOW]*** Richmond Email Update: Landed car on bottom landing, removed all oil from tank. Now in process of disassembling valve inside tank  Richmond Koonjan/Delacruz Completed disassembling valve and marking coil wires for new valve. LOTO LOOS signs posted 3/8/23 Richmond Koonjan/Delacruz/Aminov arrived. Richmond Email update: Completed removing all piping inside of tank, also removed muffler, bow valve, hose and extra piping going to the jack, placing an order at ferguson for the proper piping we need to repipe for new valve. In process of mounting new valve above tank. 

 Richmond Koonjan/Delacruz/Aminov Per our supervisor we couldn't mount the new valve with the height of the piping from the submersible pump and be able to run new piping. Ordered a longer length of piping with Ferguson as well. Will continue tomorrow after we have all the proper piping to complete mounting. Signs posted 3/8/23 LOTO.  Richmond will be upgrading the valve as well as the piping. I've requested Richmond to replace a 4ft portion of 1.5" of pipe in the pit.  Richmond Tech. DeLa Cruz/Koonjun arrived @07:00hrs to continue piping inside the tank and to valve body Richmond Email Update: (Koonjun) Received Ferguson order, installed new piping from submersible pump, new vitalic, installed maxton on top of pump side piping. Was in process of getting ready to assemble piping for jack side and come to find out they they sent the wrong jack side piping. Notified them and will be receiving correct pipes. Now in process of starting return to tank side piping.  Richmond Tech. DeLa Cruz/Koonjun Completed installing return tank side piping. Signs up 3/8/23 and LOTO  Richmond Tech. DeLa Cruz/Koonjun arrived. Richmond tech. Aminov arrived @08:00 @1103HRS [Perkhalyuk] Richmond Tech Koonjun updated via email: Completed installing new thread seal on muffler, installed muffler, installed new victaulic and new shut off valve on jack side of Maxton. Now in process of hammer drilling a hole in the wall to the shaft way for new jack side piping.  @1830HRS [Perkhalyuk] Richmond Tech Koonjun updated via email:Completed making hole in the wall from motor room to shaftway for new piping from jack side, installed new 90 degree vitalic elbow, 2 new vitalics and seals, cut 6inch PVC pipe for hole in wall, installed new piping from motor room to shaft way for jack. Started to cut old jack piping. Signs up till 3/8/23 and LOTO. 




 Richmond tech. Koonjun/De Lacruz/Aminov arrived @07:00 to continue piping in the shaft way email : Completed cutting out old jack piping completely from shaftway side, installed new jack piping in shaftway. Modified tank cover and added hinges to able to still cover tank. Ordered new coils with Martinez due to voltage being too high for this controller. Parts are en route and we will start to wire up coils to controller.  Richmond tech. Koonjun/De Lacruz/Aminov Update: Got inside tank and cleaned all shavings and anything that fell into the bottom, filled tank back up with oil. Received correct coils, installed new coils, installed pressure switch on valve, wired pressure switch, temporarily wired up each coil. Will continue tomorrow with complete wiring. Signs up till 3/8/23 and LOTO. 

 Richmond tech. Koonjun/De Lacruz arrived @07:00hrs to complete coil wiring and work on MAXTON valve body Richmond tech. Aminov arrived @08:45 Richmond tech. Koonjun/De Lacruz /Aminov Completed troubleshooting valve wiring. All coils are properly energized. Added 10 gallons of oil. Now in process of removing valve wires from controller to run new conduit from back of valve to controller.  Richmond tech. Koonjun/De Lacruz /Aminov Completed running conduit from back of valve to controller. Rewired valve and pressure switch backup. Upon arrival found car gets overshooting only in Up direction at both (middle & top) landings. Opened the cover of selector tape unit, observed visually micro switches responding for Up slowdown signals to PLC, didn't find any suspicious. Initiated manually Up slowdown transition by Output#8 (slot5)-"valv3" disconnecting, got proper Up slowdown moving. In a process next troubleshooting. WO#7866650


To make sure that Up slowdown and Down slowdown signals are indicated on the PLC-modules, moving the car on inspection and normal modes. Found on Slot#2 input #5(UPSTP) and input #6(DNSTP) appeared as designed when corresponding tape plastic cams activated the selector unit micro switches. Insufficient time to complete troubleshooting. Due to controller CPU was modified needed specialist to check controller logic. Notified ms1 Ilia. LOOS for future troubleshooting. LOTO. Signs posted to 09/13/23. W/O#7866650 - E&EMs Rybakov and Konovalov arrived at 8:48 to continue troubleshooting.

    W/O#7866650

Upon arrival before we started our selector unit switches and PLC-inputs signals investigating, we replaced for new relays all relays which had marks from oil leaking since victaulic coupling was damaged. Also checked and tightened all wires connections on relays, PLC, terminal bar. After tested elevator running, the problem still exists. In a process of selector unit switches checking. W/O#7866650
Turned off main line and check one by one all micro switches operations with electrical meter on the selector unit, nothing suspicious found, all switchable using contacts provide good continuity. Also for test reason replaced for new cams three plastic cams on selector tape that using for Up slowdown transition at middle landing. Got no effect, the Up slowdown-problem still exists. Need to be checked whole inputs sequence coming to PLC-modules (logic control). We don't have this sequence description. Notified ms1 Sergheiciuc. LOOS for future troubleshooting. LOTO. Signs posted to 09/15/23.
